<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A woman has been charged with murder following the death of a 69-year-old in Herefordshire.</p>

<p>West Mercia Police said officers were called to reports that a woman had been stabbed in the village of Cradley at about 2am on Saturday.</p>

<p>The ambulance service attended, but the woman was pronounced dead at the scene, the force added.</p>

<p>West Mercia Police said officers were called to reports that a woman had been stabbed in the village of Cradley at about 2am on Saturday</p>

<p>Police said on Sunday that Laura van Marle, 40 of no fixed address, had been charged with the murder of Susanna van Marle.</p>

<p>She was also charged with causing grievous bodily harm to a 73-year-old man during the same incident at an address in Finchers Corner, the force added.</p>

<p>Detective chief inspector Leighton Harding said: 'Our thoughts are with Susanna's friends and loved ones following this sad incident.</p>

<p>'The family are being supported by specially trained officers and have asked for privacy during this difficult time.'</p>
